<h1 class="title">Correct background bias in full dimensional space</h1>
<p>
We now assume 4bSB / 3bSB == 4bSR / 3bSR. 
</p>

<p>
If we measure and correct bias with the synthetic data. we would then only assume a double ratio holds: 
rSR / rSB (data) == rSR / rSB (synthetic data)
</p>

<div id="outline-container-orgb815d6a" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="orgb815d6a">How to measure and correct the bias</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-orgb815d6a">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Measure ration of 1D (SvB) projection  vs</li>
<li>Measure bias in full phase space with a Bkg vs Synthetic Data classifier (like FvT)</li>
</ul>

<p>
Bkg = w<sub>SvD</sub> x w<sub>FvT</sub> x w<sub>JCM</sub>
</p>
</div>
</div>



